 ride for a beverage or food. [Bierhall Brewing](Bierhall Brewing)\n\nRide 
 leader will ride at the advertised average speed\, unless at the back. Thi
 s is intended to be a no-drop group ride. You can ride ahead if you want t
 o.\n\nHelmets are mandatory\; please also plan to bring 1-2 water bottles\
 , and basic repair kit (spare tube\, tire levers\, pump/CO2 inflator).\nBe
 ing a Meetup Member does not mean you are a club member. Use this [link to
  join](https://www.lancasterbikeclub.net/content.aspx?page_id=60&club_id=2
 57148) the club.\nYour RSVP is your agreement to abide by the club's [Code
  of Conduct](https://lancbikeclub.clubexpress.com/content.aspx?page_id=22&
 club_id=257148&module_id=323984) and [Rules of the Road](https://lancbikec
 lub.clubexpress.com/content.aspx?page_id=22&club_id=257148&module_id=32515
 9)
